oracle.adf.businesseditor.objects
Interface BusinessObject

public interface BusinessObject

A business object can be customizable or reference-only. For reference-only business objects, BusinessObject.findAttribute and BusinessObject.getAttribute can be used to retrieve the attributes that can be used as list display attribute for dymanic choice list. No other methods are supported. Use isCustomizable() to identify if a business object is customizable. Note that new methods may be added to this interface without notice. Do not extend this interface for custom classes.

getAttributes

java.util.Collection<Attribute> getAttributes()
For customizable business object, this method will return all attributes for this business object. For non-customizable business object, only the attributes that can be used as list display attribute for dynamic choice list are returned. Use isCustomizable() to identify if a business object is customizable.

Returns:
collection of attributes

findFunction

BusinessObjectFunction findFunction(java.lang.String name,
                                    java.lang.String... paramTypes)
Retrieves the function with the given name for the business object. If there are multiple functions with the given name for a business object, paramTypes must be used to specify the right function to be returned. If no paramTypes is specified, a function is returned if there is only one function with the given name, or if there is one function with the name for the business object that does not contain any parameter. If no function is found for the given name, null is returned.

Parameters:
name - name of the business object function to be returned
Returns:
business object function

accept

void accept(ObjectVisitor visitor)
Visitor pattern is implemented for the business object to allow visiting each component of a business object using a custom visitor. By defining a custom visitor that implements ObjectVisitor (or extends BaseObjectVisitor), one can call BusinessObject.accept(visitor) which will transverse all the objects inside a business object.

Parameters:
visitor - The visitor object
